        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 5:57PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 555 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Milan to near
Deerfield to near Clayton. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could damage unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Adrian, Dundee, Petersburg, and Deerfield around 600 PM EDT.
Britton and Maybee around 610 PM EDT.
Tecumseh around 615 PM EDT.
Romulus around 630 PM EDT.
Milan around 645 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Newport, Whittaker,
Gibraltar, New Boston, Woodland Beach, Stony Point, Ridgeway,
Palmyra, Pleasant Lake, and Bolles Harbor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
